metadata.documentation: AWS Outposts is a fully managed service that extends AWS infrastructure, APIs, and tools to customer premises. By providing local access to AWS managed infrastructure, AWS Outposts enables customers to build and run applications on premises using the same programming interfaces as in AWS Regions, while using local compute and storage resources for lower latency and local data processing needs.

GetOutpostInstanceTypes.documentation: Lists the instance types for the specified Outpost.

exceptions.documentation: You do not have permission to perform this operation.

ListOutposts.documentation:
Create a list of the Outposts for your AWS account. Add filters to your request to return a more specific list of results. Use filters to match an Outpost lifecycle status, Availibility Zone (us-east-1a), and AZ ID (use1-az1).

If you specify multiple filters, the filters are joined with an AND, and the request returns only results that match all of the specified filters.
